author: Sophie van Bastelaer
title: SUV blocks streetcar tunnel at Queens Quay | Toronto Star
text:
The 509 and 510 streetcars are turning back at Spadina Ave. and Queens Quay this morning after an SUV blocked the tunnel leading into the Queen’s Quay station. “We'll need to cut overhead power,” Brad Ross told the Star. “Hope to clear around noon, but that could change.”
Photos tweeted from the scene by Ross showed a silver Mitsibushi on the streetcar tracks at the station platform.
This is not the first time a vehicle has mistakenly entered the streetcar tunnel.
When a similar incident happened in 2014 , Ross noted that cars entering the tunnel get hung up on the tracks, which are raised above the ground level.
Article Continued Below It took approximately eight hours for the car to be removed in 2014. In a 2015 incident, it took less than two hours. 
Ross said the driver of the SUV in today’s incident had left the scene by the time TTC officials discovered the vehicle. 
The 509 and 510 streetcar routes are currently turning back at the intersection of Spadina and Queens Quay. Shuttle buses will be running on Queens Quay between Spadina Ave. and Stadium Rd.
With files from Evelyn Kwong.
